ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have confirmed the exact failure reasons:\n\n1. **setup** flow:
After `launchApp: clearState: true`, the app is on the login page ("欢迎使用 Soc
ial World"), not the profile setup page. The flow expects "完善资料" to be visib
le immediately, but `clearState: true` cleared the auth tokens.\n\n2. **swipe_re
commendations** flow: After login with `clearState: true`, the user `13800138000
` has `profile_complete: false`, so the app redirects to `/profile-setup` instea
d of `/home`. The flow then fails at `assertVisible: id: mode_tab_nearby` becaus
e the profile setup page doesn\'t have mode tabs.\n\n3. **view_match_list** flow
: Same issue - after login, user is redirected to profile setup, so `tab_message
s` doesn\'t exist.\n\nNow, to fix these flows:\n\n**For setup.yaml:**\n- It need
s to log in first before asserting "完善资料". OR it should not use `clearState:
true`.\n- Actually, the comment says "token 已由前置 flow 保存" which means it\'
s designed to run AFTER login when not clearing state. But with `clearState: tru
e`, this is contradictory.\n- The best fix: Remove `clearState: true` so the tok
en from a previous flow (like auth/login) is preserved. But wait, if run standal
one, it would fail.\n- Alternatively, add the login steps at the beginning.\n\nL
ooking at the README and run-e2e.sh: `setup` is listed as a flow that needs back
end. The auth/login flow is separate. If they are run in sequence by Maestro, th
e `setup` flow could rely on the previous flow\'s state if it doesn\'t clear sta
te. But Maestro tests are typically run in isolation.\n\nActually, looking at Ma
estro behavior: when running multiple flows with `maestro test`, each flow runs 
sequentially on the same device. If `setup` doesn\'t clear state, the login from
`auth/login` would still be active. But the `setup.yaml` currently has `clearSta
te: true`, which resets everything.\n\nThe simplest fix for `setup.yaml` is to r
emove `clearState: true` so it can run after `auth/login` in a suite. OR, better
yet, add `runFlow: includes/login-as-test-user.yaml` at the beginning like the m
atching flows do.\n\nWait, but if I add login to setup.yaml, then after login th
e user is already on profile setup. So it would work.\n\n**For matching flows:**
\n- The root cause is that test user `13800138000` doesn\'t have a complete prof
ile.\n- Options:\n  1. Complete the profile for this user in the backend before 
running tests\n  2. Make the matching flows include profile setup first\n  3. Us
e a different test user who already has a complete profile\n\nOption 1 is best f
or making the flows work as intended. I can either:\n- Directly update the datab
ase to set `is_complete = true` for user `13800138000`\n- Or run the seed-dev sc
ript and then use one of the seeded users\n\nBut looking at the `login-as-test-u
ser.yaml`, the phone is hardcoded to `13800138000`. Changing the test user would
require updating the include file, which would affect all flows.\n\nActually, th
e most straightforward fix is to complete the profile for `13800138000` in the d
atabase. Then:\n- `setup` flow would fail because the user wouldn\'t be redirect
ed to profile setup (they\'d go to home)\n- `matching` flows would pass\n\nBut `
setup` flow is meant to test the profile setup UI. If the user already has a com
plete profile, it can\'t test that.\n\nSo the real issue is a **data conflict** 
between flows:\n- `setup` needs `13800138000` to have incomplete profile\n- `mat
ching/*` needs `13800138000` to have complete profile\n\nThis is a design issue 
with the E2E test suite. The proper solution is:\n1. `setup` flow should start f
resh, login, and then complete the profile setup. After this flow, the user has 
a complete profile.\n2. `matching/*` flows should rely on the profile being comp
lete (either by running after setup, or by having their own test user).\n\nFor a
proper fix, I should:\n1. Fix `setup.yaml` to include login steps (since it uses
`clearState: true`) and then complete the profile setup. After this flow, the te
st user will have a complete profile.\n2. For `matching/*` flows, they already i
nclude login and work IF the user has a complete profile. After running `setup`,
the user would have a complete profile. But since each matching flow uses `clear
State: true`, they start fresh and the backend still has the incomplete profile 
from before... wait, no - if `setup` completes the profile, then the backend use
r\'s profile is now complete. So subsequent matching flows would work!\n\nWait, 
but `setup.yaml` doesn\'t currently complete the profile successfully because it
fails at the first step. Let me trace through what happens:\n- `setup` runs with
`clearState: true`\n- App opens to login page\n- Flow asserts "完善资料" -> FAIL
S\n\nIf I fix `setup.yaml` to login first, then it would:\n- Login with `1380013
8000`\n- App redirects to `/profile-setup`\n- Flow completes the profile setup\n
- Backend now has `is_complete = true` for this user\n\nThen when `matching/swip
e_recommendations` runs:\n- `clearState: true` -> fresh app\n- Login with `13800
138000`\n- App checks `/auth/me` -> `profile_complete: true`\n- App redirects to
`/home`\n- Flow continues with mode tabs, swipes, etc.\n\nBut wait - the flows w
ere run in parallel or in a specific order. Looking at the test output, the orde
r was: login, edit_server_url, open_drawer, swipe_recommendations, view_match_li
st, setup. So setup ran LAST, not before matching.\n\nFor the matching flows to 
work, I need to either:\n1. Fix `setup.yaml` and ensure it runs BEFORE matching 
flows\n2. Or, pre-seed the database with a complete profile for `13800138000`\n\
nActually, looking at the Maestro test command: `find flows -name "*.yaml" | sor
t`. The sort order is alphabetical:\n- auth/login.yaml\n- devtools/edit_server_u
rl.yaml\n- devtools/open_drawer.yaml\n- matching/swipe_recommendations.yaml\n- m
atching/view_match_list.yaml\n- profile/setup.yaml\n\nSo `profile/setup.yaml` ru
ns LAST. This means matching flows run before profile setup, so even if setup wo
rked, it wouldn\'t help matching flows in the same run.\n\nThe best approach is 
to pre-seed the test data. I should:\n1. Make `13800138000` have a complete prof
ile in the backend\n2. Fix `setup.yaml` to either not use `clearState: true` (re
lying on previous login state) or to include login steps\n\nBut wait - if I make
`13800138000` have a complete profile, then `setup.yaml` can\'t test the profile
setup flow because after login the user goes directly to home.\n\nSo for a prope
r E2E suite, we need:\n- One test user for profile setup (incomplete profile)\n-
Another test user for matching (complete profile)\n\nOr, the matching flows shou
ld use a different test user.\n\nActually, looking at the PRDs, there\'s no requ
irement that all flows must pass in a single run. The important thing is to have
flows that cover the user journeys. But as an E2E test agent, I should try to ma
ke them work.\n\nLet me think about what changes to make:\n\n**Option A: Separat
e test users**\n- `login-as-test-user.yaml` keeps `13800138000` for login/auth t
ests\n- `setup.yaml` uses `13800138000` (incomplete profile)\n- Matching flows u
se a different user with complete profile, e.g., `13800000000` (from seed-dev.ts
)\n\nBut this would require creating a new include file or parameterizing the lo
gin flow.\n\n**Option B: Make setup.yaml work, and have matching flows depend on
setup**\n- Remove `clearState: true` from `setup.yaml` so it runs after `auth/lo
gin` preserving the logged-in state\n- But then `setup.yaml` can\'t run standalo
ne\n\n**Option C: Pre-seed complete profile for 13800138000 and fix setup.yaml**
\n- This makes setup.yaml fail because user goes to home instead of setup\n\nAct
ually, looking at the task instructions: "对比 PRD 需求和已有 flow，列出缺失的用
户旅程" and "如果缺少 flow → 你需要创建新的 flow". But the main task is to run t
ests, analyze failures, and fix flows.\n\nGiven the constraints, I think the mos
t pragmatic fix is:\n\n1. **Fix `setup.yaml`**: Add login steps at the beginning
(like matching flows do), since it uses `clearState: true`. This makes it a stan
dalone flow. Also check if the date picker uses "OK" or "确定".\n\n2. **Fix matc
hing flows**: Either complete the profile for `13800138000` in the DB before run
ning tests, OR make matching flows use a different user with a complete profile.
\n\nSince the task says the environment should be ready, and the backend is runn
ing, let me check if I can just update the database directly. But modifying the 
backend DB is kind of an environment change, not a flow fix.\n\nActually, lookin
g at the `seed-dev.ts`, I could run it to seed the database, and then update the
`13800138000` user\'s profile to be complete. But then setup.yaml would fail.\n\
nAlternatively, I can make the matching flows use a different phone number. Let 
me check if the seeded users have passwords/codes. Looking at seed-dev.ts, it do
esn\'t create SMS codes. So I\'d need to seed SMS codes for those users too.\n\n
This is getting complicated. Let me step back.\n\nThe simplest fix that makes th
e most flows pass:\n\n1. **Fix `profile/setup.yaml`**: Add `runFlow: includes/lo
gin-as-test-user.yaml` after `launchApp` (and keep `clearState: true`). This mak
es it a standalone flow.\n\n2. **For matching flows**: The real issue is test da
ta. Since `13800138000` doesn\'t have a complete profile, and the matching flows
use this user, they fail. I should complete the profile for `13800138000` in the
database by running the setup flow first, or by directly updating the DB.\n\nAct
ually, wait! If I run `setup.yaml` first (after fixing it), it will complete the
profile for `13800138000`. Then in subsequent matching flows, even though they u
se `clearState: true`, the backend still has the complete profile for this user.
So the matching flows would work!\n\nBut the flows run in alphabetical order: ma
tching flows run BEFORE profile/setup. So in a single `maestro test` run with al
l flows, matching would still fail.\n\nHowever, the `run-e2e.sh` script doesn\'t
run flows in any particular order guarantee. And we could run them individually.
\n\nFor the purpose of this task, I should:\n1. Fix the flows to be correct\n2. 
Run them again to verify\n3. Report the results\n\nLet me fix the flows:\n\n**Fi
x 1: `profile/setup.yaml`**\n- Add login steps after `launchApp`\n- The date pic
ker `tapOn: "OK"` might need to be changed to `tapOn: "确定"` depending on local
