ve navigated away and we wouldn\'t see the countdown continuing to tick. But the
screenshot was taken ~17 seconds after the last tap, and the countdown shows 33s
. \n\nSince the countdown started at 60s, and it shows 33s, that means ~27 secon
ds have elapsed since the countdown started. The flow tapped `获取验证码` early 
on, then did several other steps, then tapped `登录` three times. The total time
from `获取验证码` to screenshot should be around 15-20 seconds. 60 - 27 = 33. So
~27 seconds elapsed. That seems about right.\n\nBut here\'s the key insight: the
app is STILL on the login page. This means the login button tap is definitely no
t triggering navigation.\n\nLet me try using `adb shell input tap` directly. I\'
ll create a flow that fills the fields with Maestro, then uses a `runScript` or 
I can just run adb separately after Maestro pauses.\n\nActually, Maestro has a `
runScript` command that can execute shell scripts. But it\'s easier to just use 
`adb shell input tap` in parallel.\n\nWait, I just had another idea. Maybe the i
ssue is that the `tapOn` in Maestro for Flutter `ElevatedButton` doesn\'t work w
hen the button is inside a `BlocBuilder` because Maestro is looking for the text
"登录" but finding it on the inner `Text` widget, not the `ElevatedButton` itsel
f. In Flutter\'s semantics tree, `ElevatedButton` should merge the child\'s sema
ntics. But maybe there\'s an issue with how the semantics are exposed.\n\nActual
ly, looking at the Maestro logs, when it taps on "登录", it finds:\n```\nUiEleme
nt(treeNode=TreeNode(attributes={text=, accessibilityText=登录, hintText=, ignor
